The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 Classical confluence

 ITC Sangeet Research Academy hosts its annual ITC Sangeet Sammelan, a music conference that promises to provide an enchanting experience to connoisseurs of Hindustani classical music. To be inaugurated today at 6 pm, it commences with the presentation of the ITC Award to renowned vocalist of the Agra gharana, Pandit Dinkar Kaikini. The performers at the three-day festival include several distinguished exponents of vocal and instrumental music. The inaugural evenings programme begins with a vocal performance by Sameehan Ulhas Kashalkar, protege of his illustrious father, eminent vocalist Pandit Ulhas Kashalkar. The programme also features a flute recital by master of the dhrupad, khayal and tantrakari ang, Rupak Kulkarni, disciple of flute maestro Hariprasad Chaurasia. The concluding item of the evening is a vocal recital by Pandit Ajoy Chakraborty (picture above), a popular concert vocalist and one of the most celebrated artistes of his generation.

 Event: ITC Sangeet Sammelan, Indian classical music festival 

When: December 8 - December 10, 6 pm onwards 

Where: ITC Sangeet Research Academy lawns 

